def chi_square(data:pd.DataFrame,a:str,b:str,alpha:float = 0.05) -> str:
    crossTab = pd.crosstab(data[a],data[b])
    prob = {}
    for i in crossTab.axes[1]:
        prob[i] = sum(crossTab[i])/data.shape[0]
    for i in crossTab.axes[0]:
        prob[i] = sum(crossTab.loc[i])/data.shape[0]
    expected = {}
    for i in crossTab.axes[1]:
        for j in crossTab.axes[0]:
            expected[j+' '+i] = prob[i]*prob[j]*data.shape[0]
    chisquare = 0
    for i in crossTab.axes[1]:
        for j in crossTab.axes[0]:
            chisquare += (expected[j+' ' +i] - crossTab.loc[j,i])**2/expected[j+' ' +i]
    df = (crossTab.shape[0]-1)*(crossTab.shape[1] - 1)
    critical = stats.chi2.ppf(1-alpha,df)
    if chisquare < critical:
        return 'failed to reject null for {} and {}'.format(a,b)
    return'reject null for {} and {}'.format(a,b)

def summary(data:pd.DataFrame,cols:list[str]) -> pd.DataFrame:
    summ = {'cols':[],'outliers':[],'outliers_percentage':[]}
    for i in cols:
        q1,q3 = np.percentile(data[i],[15,75])
        IQR = q3-q1
        min_ = q1 - 1.5*IQR
        max_ = q3 + 1.5*IQR
        vals = data[(data[i]>max_) | (data[i]<min_)].shape[0]
        percent = format(vals*100/data.shape[0],'.2f')
        summ['cols'].append(i)
        summ['outliers'].append(vals)
        summ['outliers_percentage'].append(percent)
    return pd.DataFrame(summ)
summary(data=data,cols=cols)

def normalize(data:pd.DataFrame,cols:list[str]):
    for i in cols:
        mean = data[i].mean()
        sd = data[i].std()
        data[i] = data[i].apply(lambda x: (x-mean)/sd)
def min_max(data:pd.DataFrame,cols:list[str]):
    for i in cols:
        max_ = data[i].max()
        min_ = data[i].min()
        data[i] = data[i].apply(lambda x: (x-min_)/(max_-min_))
min_max(data=data,cols=cols)
